(1, 7, 'What_is_the_best_operating_system_for_programming?', '<p>I have been using windows 10 pro for a while now. And am kind of like I want to know which operating system is best for programming.</p><p>And &nbsp;most of my mates too are like Linux funs.</p><p>I don''t have problem with using windows10 but am kind of curious.</p><p>Because I learned there are about 8 operating systems<a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_operating_systems">[]</a>.</p>', '', 'Computing', 'programming,OS', NULL, '2020-04-09 11:05:54', '2020-05-31 04:51:16'),
(2, 7, 'Maya_and_Blender_which_one_is_more_recommend_to_learn?', '<p>I am arts student doing communication design and am kind of confuse which one to learn. Knowing that one is open source and one is paid application.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Art', 'Maya,Blender,Art', 0, '2020-04-09 11:26:09', '2020-04-25 12:44:02'),
(3, 7, 'How_can_I_promote_my_art_and_get_it_sold_online?', '<p>I am an artist and I want to sell my art online. Despite using several websites to sell my art, I''m unsuccessful.</p>', '', 'Art', 'online,website,Art', 1, '2020-04-09 11:40:15', '2020-04-25 12:53:47'),
(4, 7, 'What_is_the_difference_between_art_and_design?', '<p>Art and design is inside museums and art galleries, so is the difference in the education system, or or field work.</p>', '', 'Art', 'Art,Design', NULL, '2020-04-09 11:46:56', '2020-04-25 12:49:44'),
(5, 7, 'What_relationship_facts_should_everyone_know_before_getting_married?', '<p>I am just getting myself into a <strong>relationship </strong>is my first time and I don''t want to brow it up. Any advice!!.</p><p>What should I know first be I get into it.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Others', 'relationship', NULL, '2020-05-03 09:34:04', '2020-05-03 09:34:04'),
(6, 7, 'Why_do_self-taught_programmers_seem_to_do_be_better_than_those_with_a_computer_science_degree?', '<p>I an planning on going to university to offer <strong>computer science</strong>, but am not seeing any motivation from my friends already there studying <strong>computer science</strong>. I don''t know why must of good programmers I know learned them themselves. why self-taught programmers seem to be better than those with computer science degree or am the one not see it well.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Computing', 'Programming,self-taught', NULL, '2020-05-03 10:30:21', '2020-05-04 18:11:31'),
(7, 7, 'Is_it_too_late_to_learn_programming_and_find_a_good_job_at_the_age_of_30?', '<p>I am wondering if at my age i can start learning programming and get a job, or is too much of mathematics that i can''t contain at this stage of life. And i did not read computer science or anything related to computing but i did art at &nbsp;the university, so am good at animation like using Maya and blender.&nbsp;</p><p>I want to add programming to my career.</p>', '', 'Computing', 'programming,mathematics', NULL, '2020-05-03 10:39:09', '2020-05-03 10:39:09'),
(8, 7, 'How_do_I_know_if_she_really_likes_me_and_not_just_faking?', '<p>There is this lady that most often come to my place but i don''t know whether she likes me or just joking, I really likes her but am afraid to tell her, she might turn me down and our friendship may be ruin, She laugh a lot at my jokes even if is not all that funny, and she can not look straight into my eyes. Am confuse whether to make a bold step or just let it go. But i really like her.</p>', '', 'Others', 'Relationship', NULL, '2020-05-03 10:54:53', '2020-05-09 09:44:23'),
(9, 7, 'What_is_the_most_convenient_way_to_study?', '<p>I am in the same room with two of my course mate. I study far more than them, but exams they perform far more than me. I don''t understand is it that am not doing it right or there is more convenient way to study that i don''t know.</p>', '', 'Others', 'Study,Exams', NULL, '2020-05-03 11:12:56', '2020-05-03 11:12:56'),
(10, 4, 'what_is_the_difference_between_software_engineering_and_software_development?', '<p>I have a friend who is majoring in software engineering and they are only teaching him how to build &nbsp;software. &nbsp;So what is the difference between them.</p>', '', 'Computing', 'Software,Engineering', NULL, '2020-05-14 19:54:10', '2020-05-14 19:54:10'),
(11, 2, 'what_is_the_difference_between_content_errors_and_coverage_errors?', '<p>If the content of the survey is wrong then differently coverage too is wrong. So What is the difference between them.</p>', '', 'Science', 'Mathematics,Statistics,Demography', NULL, '2020-04-24 22:44:58', '2020-05-15 22:44:58'),
(12, 2, 'Why_was_the_preliminary_result_of_the_2010_population_cessus_of_Ghana_adjusted_2%_upward?', '<p>The preliminary result of the 2010 population cusses of Ghana was adjusted 2% upward, And it was use for decision making is it not bias to inject the result of statistics.</p>', '', 'Science', 'Statistics,Mathematics,Demography', NULL, '2020-04-02 00:43:01', '2020-05-15 22:52:28'),
(13, 2, 'You_believe_that_a_set_of_data_is_the_realization_of_a_stationary_process_where_the_white_noise_are_purely_random.', '<p>You believe that a set of data is the realization of a stationary process where the white noise are purely random.&nbsp;</p><p>You have calculated the following:</p><figure class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>lags,<i>h</i></th><th>0</th><th>1</th><th>2</th><th>3</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><th><i>y</i>(h)</th><td>1</td><td>-0.25</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><th><i>p(h)</i></th><td>&nbsp;-&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;-</td><td>&nbsp;-</td><td>&nbsp;-</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Calculate:</p><ol><li>Identify the stationary process for the set of data.</li><li>Calculate the PACF at lag 2.</li><li>Estimate the coefficient in (i).</li><li>Which value of the parameter do you think you should choose? Why?</li></ol>', '', 'Science', 'Time_Series,Mathematics,Statistics,Actuarial_science', NULL, '2020-05-23 23:05:12', '2020-05-23 23:08:14'),
(14, 2, 'A_water_company_wishes_to_estimate_the_total_amount_of_water_used_by_its_domestic_consumers.', '<p>A water company wishes to estimate the total amount of water used by its domestic consumers. Its domestic business serves 400,000 households altogether and is divided into four regions. As an initial exercise, before the main survey, a simple random sample of 50 metered households was selected in each region, and for each household the amount y of water used (in megaliths) over the past 12 months was determined by inspecting its water bill. Estimates of the means and standard deviations of y in each region, based on this sample of 200 households,</p><p>are as follows.</p><figure class="table"><table><tbody><tr><td>Region</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>No. of households (in thousands)</td><td>160</td><td>110</td><td>80</td><td>50</td></tr><tr><td>Sample mean</td><td>0.131</td><td>0.095</td><td>0.112</td><td>0.172</td></tr><tr><td>Sample standard deviation</td><td>0.022</td><td>0.015</td><td>0.032</td><td>0.064</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Comment briefly on the merits of using stratified random sampling for this survey.</li><li>Based on the results given above, estimate the total domestic water consumption over the past 12 months, and obtain an estimate of the standard error of your estimator.</li><li>For the main survey, discuss briefly why you might choose optimal allocation rather than proportional allocation. (You may assume that the cost of sampling any unit is constant.)</li><li>Use optimal allocation to calculate the total sample size and the allocation needed to estimate total domestic water consumption over the past 12 months, to within 600 megaliths with 95% confidence.</li></ol>', '', 'Science', 'Mathematics, Sample_survey,Statistics', NULL, '2020-05-25 08:48:18', '2020-05-25 08:48:18'),
