(1, 13, '<p>A <strong>software engineer</strong> takes the software needs of end users into account and consequently develops or designs new applications. Furthermore, software engineering may involve the process of analyzing existing software and modifying it to meet current application needs.</p><p>As <strong>computer hardware</strong> becomes cheaper, the focus transfers to s<strong>oftware systems</strong>. Large software systems may be more complex than the hardware used to run them, so there is great demand for best practices and <strong>engineering processes</strong> that can be applied to software development. There must be discipline and control during software engineering, much like any complex engineering endeavor.</p><p>In modern consumer electronics, devices in direct competition often have similar hardware and processing power, but the user experience will vary greatly depending on the software being used.&nbsp;</p><p>Reference from: <a href="https://www.techopedia.com/definition/13296/software-engineering">https://www.techopedia.com/definition/13296/software-engineering</a></p><h2>WHILES</h2><p><strong>Software development</strong> is an <strong>iterative logical process</strong> that aims to <strong>create a computer coded or programmed software</strong> to address a unique business or personal objective, goal or process. Software development is generally a planned initiative that consists of various steps or stages that result in the creation of operational software.</p><p><strong>Software development</strong> is primarily achieved through <strong>computer programming</strong>, which is carried out by a <strong>software programmer</strong> and includes processes such as initial research, data flow design, process flow design, flow charts, technical documentation, software testing, debugging and other software architecture techniques. This is known as the <strong>software development life cycle</strong> (SDLC).</p><p>Reference from: <a href="https://www.techopedia.com/definition/16431/software-development">https://www.techopedia.com/definition/16431/software-development</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 11, 0, '2020-05-15 01:04:12', '2020-05-15 01:04:12'),
(2, 13, '<p>OK I am fortunate to start programming early, but for all I know is. I have been teaching programming for 17 years now and most of my student I teach turned to be aged. Though age matter but not when you can still think of logic and problems. Programming is about solving problem. If you think you have that potential then give it a try.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>What most aged face most as a problem is time</strong>, programming is all about time. And at the age of 30 you may be having a wife and kids, &nbsp;that is when the problem comes. Giving you kids and wife time and programming too time is a bit though, am not saying programmers don''t marry.</p><p>During the time of learning, it requires a lot of time.</p><p>If you think you can balance that then you are very free to go.</p><h4>GOOD LUCK</h4>', 8, 0, '2020-05-15 01:20:40', '2020-05-15 01:20:40'),
(3, 13, '<p><strong>Self-taught programmers</strong> only focus on the programming aspect. Is kind of hard to learn or understand all the programming or a single programming language. And <strong>self-taught</strong> tend to learn only the ones they will need. I have come to contact with some <strong>self-taught programmers</strong> and when you ask them any question concerning what they are doing, they find it difficult to answer. The don''t understand it more as those of <strong>computer science </strong>students .</p><p><strong>University</strong> try to train student to be able to work on other fields, so whiles the <strong>self-taught</strong> is focusing of learning programming algorithms the <strong>computer science</strong> student will also be think on how to write his economics or English exams.</p><p>They learn more and in tend they understand the concepts of the programming and they don''t realize Solly on becoming a <a href="https://tekporacademy.tk/forum/questions/what_is_the_difference_between_software_engineering_and_software_development?">software engineering or software development.</a></p>', 7, 0, '2020-05-15 01:46:41', '2020-05-15 01:46:41'),
(4, 13, '<p>This is too general question, I think is the one you are most comfortable with that supports the tools comfortably.&nbsp;</p><p>I have been using Linux of quite a long time, So if you present me with windows operating system or Mac-OS I may have some difficulties. And I think Linux serve my needs.</p><p>So just look for the one that serve you needs. The good thing right now is that there''s a lot of convergence between operating systems that make moving between them a lot easier than it was just a few years ago.</p><p>When it comes to web programming, Linux (especially Arch Linux + lightweight window manager) is good. I used to use Arch Linux as my daily Desktop environment. It has really great performance, Docker compatibility, and close to production environment.</p><p>And choosing operating system, there are things you need to consider, Linux is an open source and might not be good for company development in case of system error and Linux in it way was perfectly design for team development.</p><p>Windows on the other hand is not and open source operating system so in case of system support is recommended.</p><p>Linux has a lot of programming advantages in term of per-installed programming languages like PHP, Python, Perl and many more.</p>', 1, 0, '2020-05-15 02:04:22', '2020-05-15 02:04:22'),
(5, 19, '<p><strong>Coverage errors</strong> arise from failure to cover adequately all components of the population being studied.</p><p><strong>Coverage errors</strong> are due to divergences between the target population and the frame. <strong>Coverage errors</strong> include over-coverage, under-coverage and misclassification.</p><p><strong>Coverage errors</strong> is the error in an estimate that results from failure to include specified units in the conduct of a survey (under-coverage), and inclusion of some units erroneously either because of a defective frame or because of inclusion of unspecified units or inclusion of specified units more than once in the actual survey (over-coverage).</p><p>Whiles <strong>Content Errors</strong> are Errors of observation or objective measurement, of recording, of imputation, or of other processing which results in associating a wrong value of the characteristic with a specified unit.These are errors associated with the characteristics of the population or person, e.g. age, sex, number of children born, etc.</p><p>Besides from the errors due to carelessness or mistakes in judgment in a census or vital statistic registration, errors of coverage or content or both can arise at any step from initiation of an original record publication to the final tabulation or final record.</p><p>Sources of Errors are:</p><blockquote><ol><li>1. <strong>The respondent.</strong></li></ol></blockquote><p>– Ignorance – lack of knowledge of correct ages</p><p>– Superstition – infants not to be countered, etc</p><p>– Deliberate intentions</p><p>– Fear</p><p>– Behavior pattern of society – people not interested in data</p><p>– Some house are not to be entered</p><blockquote><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2. <strong>The recorder/ enumerator /investigator .</strong></p></blockquote><p>– Lack of skilled personnel</p><p>– Method of administering, interpreting and recording answers (translating manual into local languages</p><p>– Lack of motivation – enumerators not calling back and relying on neighbors for information or fill questionnaire themselves and may not use the historical calendars</p><blockquote><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3. <strong>Administrative Errors</strong></p></blockquote><p>– No sufficient time allowed for activities and preparation – design of questionnaire, pilot survey, logistics, maps, etc.</p><p>– No proper demarcation of enumeration areas</p><p>– Inadequate stock of questionnaire – instances of shortage of questionnaire in some areas during 2010 census</p><p>– Coding errors</p><p>Reference from book: <a href="https://tekporacademy.tk/Bookname/Demographic_Method_and_Data_Analysis">https://tekporacademy.tk/Bookname/Demographic_Method_and_Data_Analysis</a></p>', 12, 0, '2020-04-24 22:44:58', '2020-05-15 23:39:01'),
(6, 19, '<p>Ghana as at 2010 do not have enough resource to undertake very good census.</p><p>So it was adjusted 2% upward to account for:</p><blockquote><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> &nbsp;1. Lack of field questionnaire.</strong></p></blockquote><p>– Inadequate stock of questionnaire – instances of shortage of questionnaire in some areas during 2010 census.</p><blockquote><p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> 2. Lack of interest of the society in value of data</strong></p></blockquote><p>– The Lack of interest in value of data – society not seeing the essence of data and in tend &nbsp;do not give correct data or not taking part at all.</p><blockquote><p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 3. Lack of motivation of enumerators</strong></p></blockquote><p>– The Lack of motivation – enumerators not calling back and relying on neighbors for information or fill questionnaire themselves and may not use the historical calendars.</p><blockquote><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>4. Lack of up to date information.</strong></p></blockquote><p>– logistics and maps problem - No proper demarcation of enumeration areas and some areas were left-out.</p><blockquote><p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;5. Coding errors.</strong></p></blockquote><p>– Computing errors – The problem of computing arise as some data were not inputted for statistics.</p><blockquote><p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong> &nbsp;6. Traditional believes.</strong></p></blockquote><p>–Superstition – infants not to be countered, Some house are not to be entered, etc</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reference from book: <a href="https://tekporacademy.tk/Bookname/Demographic_Method_and_Data_Analysis">https://tekporacademy.tk/Bookname/Demographic_Method_and_Data_Analysis</a></p>', 13, 0, '2020-04-02 00:43:01', '2020-05-16 00:43:01'),
(7, 12, '<p>From <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org">Wikipedia</a> ;&nbsp;</p><p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Art"><strong>Art</strong></a> is a diverse range of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_behavior">human activities</a> in creating visual, auditory or performing artifacts (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artworks">artworks</a>), expressing the author''s <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imagination">imaginative</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concept">conceptual</a> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idea">ideas</a>, or technical skill, intended to be appreciated for their beauty or emotional power. Other activities related to the production of works of art include the criticism of art, the study of the history of art, and the aesthetic dissemination of art.</p><p>The three classical branches of art are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Painting">painting</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sculpture">sculpture</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Architecture">architecture</a>. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Music">Music</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theatre">theater</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Film">film</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dance">dance</a>, and other <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Performing_arts">performing arts</a>, as well as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literature">literature</a> and other media such as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interactive_media">interactive media</a>, are included in a broader definition of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_arts">the arts</a>. Until the 17th century, <i>art</i> referred to any skill or mastery and was not differentiated from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Craft">crafts</a> or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sciences">sciences</a>. In modern usage after the 17th century, where aesthetic considerations are paramount, the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fine_art">fine arts</a> are separated and distinguished from acquired skills in general, such as the decorative or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Applied_arts">applied arts</a>.</p><p>Though the definition of what constitutes art is disputed and has changed over time, general descriptions mention an idea of imaginative or technical skill stemming from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agency_(philosophy)">human agency</a> and creation. The nature of art and related concepts, such as creativity and interpretation, are explored in a branch of philosophy known as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aesthetics">aesthetics</a>.</p><p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design"><strong>Design</strong></a> on the other hand, is a plan or specification for the construction of an object or system or for the implementation of an activity or process, or the result of that plan or specification in the form of a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prototype">prototype</a>, product or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Process">process</a>. The verb <i>to design</i> expresses the process of developing a design. In some cases, the direct construction of an object without an explicit prior plan (such as in craft-work, some engineering, coding, and graphic design) may also be considered to be a design activity. The design usually has to satisfy certain <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal">goals</a> and constraints, may take into account aesthetic, functional, economic, or sociopolitical considerations, and is expected to interact with a certain <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Environment_(systems)">environment</a>. Major examples of designs include <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blueprint">architectural blueprints</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Engineering_drawing">engineering drawings</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business_process">business processes</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circuit_diagram">circuit diagrams</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pattern_(sewing)">sewing patterns</a>.</p><p>The person who produces a design is called a <i>designer</i>, which is a term generally used for people who work professionally in one of the various design areas—usually specifying which area is being dealt with (such as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Textile_design">textile designer</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fashion_design">fashion designer</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Product_design">product designer</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concept_design">concept designer</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_design">web designer</a> (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Website_design">website designer</a>) or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interior_design">interior designer</a>), but also others such as architects and engineers. A designer''s sequence of activities is called a design process, possibly using <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design_methods">design methods</a>. The process of creating a design can be brief (a quick sketch) or lengthy and complicated, involving considerable research, negotiation, reflection, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conceptual_model">modeling</a>, interactive adjustment and re-design.</p>', 4, -1, '2020-05-19 10:13:15', '2020-09-16 17:53:50'),
(8, 12, '<p>Yes, that is the work of the web.</p><p>&nbsp;You can design a website or mobile application that you can have all for your art works there with price tags and share it around. &nbsp;Website is such that they don''t pay you for users using internet data on &nbsp;you site, You only get pay when you sell or advertise on your blog.</p><p>Asking how to promote, I will say design a website or mobile application that you can put all your art works there and sell.</p>', 3, 0, '2020-05-19 10:27:27', '2020-05-19 10:27:27'),
(9, 12, '<p><strong>Blender</strong> is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_and_open-source_software">free and open-source</a> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_computer_graphics">3D computer graphics</a> software tool-set used for creating <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animation">animated films</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_effects">visual effects</a>, art, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_printing">3D printed</a> models, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_graphics">motion graphics</a>, interactive 3D applications, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_game">computer games</a>. Blender''s features include <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_modeling">3D modeling</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UV_mapping">UV unwrapping</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texture_mapping">texturing</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raster_graphics_editor">raster graphics editing</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skeletal_animation">rigging and skinning</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid_simulation">fluid and smoke simulation</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Particle_system">particle</a> simulation, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soft_body_dynamics">soft body</a> simulation, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_sculpting">sculpting</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_animation">animating</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Match_moving">match moving</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rendering_(computer_graphics)">rendering</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_graphics">motion graphics</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Video_editing_software">video editing</a>, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compositing">compositing</a>.</p><p><strong>Autodesk Maya</strong>, commonly shortened to just <strong>Maya</strong>, is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_computer_graphics_software">3D computer graphics application</a> that runs on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows">Windows</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MacOS">mac-OS</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux">Linux</a>, originally developed by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alias_Systems_Corporation">Alias Systems Corporation</a> (formerly Alias|Wavefront) and currently owned and developed by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autodesk,_Inc.">Autodesk</a>. It is used to create assets for interactive 3D applications (including video games), animated films, TV series, and visual effects.</p><p>When I start doing animation, I started with blender for many reasons. Like blender is free Maya is not, etc.</p><p>Most industries do not hire blender animators, they preferred Maya to blender.&nbsp;</p><p>Since blender is free and open source you don''t get system support. &nbsp;Maya is not open source so in case of any error you can contact them have it fix for you.</p><p>Do learn animation for job Maya is recommended, to learn for fun blender is highly recommended.</p><p>On the bright side moving from some software to other is very easy especially moving from blender to Maya or any other 3D computer graphics application.</p>', 2, 0, '2020-05-19 11:01:59', '2020-05-19 11:01:59'),
(10, 4, '<ol><li>The realization is a MOVING AVERAGE PROCESS OF ODER ONE MA(1).<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Partial Autocorrelation function PACF<br><strong>CHECK THE ATTACHED IMAGE.</strong></li><li>MOVING AVERAGE PROCESS OF ODER ONE MA(1). With zero(0) mean and a constant finite variance.<br>A time series { Yt } which satisfies</li></ol><blockquote><p>Y t = Ө1 et-1 + e t where et is a white noise.</p><p>The variance of the MA(1) process is computed as:</p><p>var( Y t ) = var(Ө1 et-1 + e t) = (1+ Ө1 2 )Ծe2&nbsp;</p><p>var( Y t ) = Ɣ0 = (1+ Ө1 2 )Ծe2 ;</p><p>We now compute the autocovariance function ACF(1) at lag 1:</p><p>Y tY t-1 = Ө1 Y t-1 et-1 + Y t-1 e t&nbsp;</p><p>E(Y tY t-1)= E( Ө1 Y t-1 et-1 + Y t-1 e t)</p><p>E(Y tY t-1) = e t e t-1 + Ө1 e t e t-1 + Ө1 e t-1 + Ө1 e t e t-1</p><p>E(Y tY t-1) = Ɣ1 = 0 + 0 + Ө1 Ծe2 + 0 = Ө1 Ծe2&nbsp;</p><p>Ɣ1 = -0.25</p><p><i>p</i>1 = -0.25</p><p>Ө = -0.268</p><p>The MA(1) process with zero mean is given by</p><p>Y t = -0.268et-1 + e t</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 4. The autocorrelation function;</p><blockquote><p>The order of a MOVING AVERAGE MA(q) process is determined by the The autocorrelation function ACF.</p><p>An MA(q) process has its ACF cutting off after lag q.</p></blockquote><p>REFERENCED BOOK:&nbsp;<a href="https://tekporacademy.tk/Bookname/Times_series_Analysis">Times_series_Analysis</a></p></br/><p class="ftco-animate"><a href="../../../answerAttachment/1590369851-330-attachment-25-05-2020-01-24-11-Screenshot_2020-05-23 Screenshot(2).png" class="gallery image-popup img d-flex align-items-center" title="on computer, right ckick and select view image to see full image"><img id="image" src="../../../answerAttachment/1590369851-330-attachment-25-05-2020-01-24-11-Screenshot_2020-05-23 Screenshot(2).png" width="100%" height="400px"> </a></p><br/></br/>', 14, 0, '2020-05-24 06:40:54', '2020-05-25 08:24:12'),
(11, 11, '<ul><li><strong>Start asking questions</strong></li><li><strong>Brainstorm with classmates and friends.&nbsp;</strong><ul><li>Engage the brains of other people. Brainstorm on issues along your field. For more details on how this is done, read my previous post on <a href="https://simplyeducate.me/2012/11/10/brainstorming-to-generate-ideas-for-research/">brainstorming</a>.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Join research groups.</strong><ul><li>If you are still in your junior years, you may join those graduating students while they conduct their research. This will enable you to see some areas which have not been explored. Questions may also arise during the research process that may bring you to develop a research topic of your own.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Review your lecture note&nbsp;</strong></li><li><strong>Do some background reading.</strong> To generate a topic for a <a href="https://www.wikihow.com/Write-a-Research-Paper">research paper,</a> you have to do a little reading first. If your class is reading an introductory book, you can get an idea of what you like. If not, you can read one on your own. Browse it until you find something that catches your attention.<ul><li>Read as much as you can. At this stage, it’s okay to use search engines and sites like Wikipedia. They will give you enough information to figure out if you like a topic.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Start narrowing down your area.</strong> Once you have completed your reading, it''s time to start narrowing down your areas of interest. You can do this by picking a topic that you like, then delving deeper and deeper into that topic until you find something worth writing about.<a href="https://www.wikihow.com/Generate-the-Best-Research-Topics#_note-1">[1]</a>&nbsp;<ul><li>For example, if your class is "Introduction to Psychology", you could narrow down your area to behavioral psychology, based on your reading.</li><li>Once you''ve established a general area of interest, you can start narrowing your area even further. For example, within the field of behavioral psychology, you may decide to focus only on the work of B. F. Skinner.</li><li>Make a list of all the things that interest you within your narrowed topic. Maybe you find classical conditioning interesting, or perhaps you find a particular experiment fascinating.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Make a bubble map to help with the idea-generating process.</strong> Take out a blank sheet of paper. Draw your main idea in a bubble in the middle of the paper. Draw a line going off the main idea, then make another bubble. In that bubble, put something related to the main idea that you find interesting.&nbsp;<ul><li>Keep drawing bubbles and adding additional ideas. Sometimes, you will add your ideas on to secondary bubbles instead of the main one. You can keep expanding an idea out. In fact, it’s a good idea to focus on an idea that continues to branch off the main one if you find it interesting.</li><li>For example, in your main bubble you might put “B. F. Skinner and Behavioral Psychology.” Then in one secondary bubble, you might put "the principle of reinforcement", while in another you put "radical behaviorism".</li></ul></li></ul><p>Reference from <a href="https://www.wikihow.com/Generate-the-Best-Research-Topics">wikihow</a> &nbsp;&amp; <a href="https://simplyeducate.me/2013/03/19/10-tips-to-generate-your-research-topic/">simplyeducate</a></p>', 23, 0, '2020-05-31 04:44:13', '2020-05-31 04:44:13'),
(12, 4, '<p><strong>Experimental research design</strong> is a study that strictly adheres to a scientific research design. It includes a hypothesis, a variable that can be manipulated by the researcher, and variables that can be measured, calculated and compare. The researcher collect data and the result will either support or reject the hypothesis.</p><p>Observation research is also know as field research is a type of non-experimental research in which a researcher observes ongoing behavior.</p><p><strong>Experimental research design differ from observational research in the sense that.</strong> Experimental research measure, calculate and compare data and the result will either reject or support the hypotheses. Whiles the observational research design only observe and compare data and the result will either reject or support the hypotheses.</p>', 21, 0, '2020-05-31 05:16:39', '2020-05-31 05:16:39'),
(13, 4, '<p><strong>Difference between basic and applied research</strong></p><p>Basic research, also called pure research or fundamental research, has the scientific research aim to improve scientific theories for improved understanding or prediction of natural or other phenomena while applied research in turn, uses scientific theories to develop technology or techniques to intervene and alter natural or other phenomena.</p><p>Reference from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_research">https://en.wikipedia.org</a></p>', 19, 0, '2020-05-31 05:24:28', '2020-05-31 05:24:28'),
